// @test regression/INV075-postfix-leading-wrap-multiple-of-4
// @description Postfix continuations that start with a dot or call paren at multiple-of-4 indent are TV's CE10013 mismatched-input diagnostics anchored at the leading token, not generic parser errors. Non-multiple-of-4 postfix wraps still join. See TODO #45.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=6, message=/Mismatched input "\." expecting "end of line without line continuation"/
// @expects error: line=10, message=/Mismatched input "\(" expecting "end of line without line continuation"/
//@version=6
indicator("INV075 postfix leading wrap")
good = str
 .length("abc")
badDot = str
    .length("abc")
f = math.max
 (1, 2)
badCall = math.max
    (1, 2)
plot(good + f + badDot + badCall)
